E%D8%B3%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become good, to better, to improve"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become pleasant or agreeable"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become pleasant or agreeable; to be or become beautiful, to beautify","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to improve, to ameliorate, to better, to polish, to embellish"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to perfect"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prettify, to beautify, to adorn, to make attractive"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bedeck, to ornament, to decorate, to deck out, to garnish"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shape up, tidy up (hair or beard)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to apply cosmetics, to put on makeup"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to amend"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fake"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَسُنَ (ḥasuna) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"goodness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prettiness, beauty, loveliness, shapeliness, comeliness, gorgeousness, pulchritude"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"handsomeness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"charm, charms, glamor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"glory"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nicety, fineness, grace, gracefulness, foppery"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fineness, efficiency, efficacy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"good, fine, well"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"agreeable, pleasant, nice, well-favored"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pretty, beautiful, lovely, comely, sightly, shapely, gorgeous, fair"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"handsome, good-looking, magnificent"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"well-turned"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"radiant, glad, charming"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"graceful, fine, dainty"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"okay, all right"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"Hasan, acceptable"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Hasan or Hassan"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Ḥasan ibn ʕaliyy, the grandson and a revered companion of Muhammad, and the 2nd Shia Imam."}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Causative form II verb derived from the form I verb حَسُنَ (ḥasuna, “to be good”)."},"ipa":["/ħa.san/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8000","headword_ar":"حَسُنَ","root":"Hsn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.,) which may also be written and pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasona","text_ar":"حَسْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the dammeh suppressed, (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasana","text_ar":"حَسَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonN","text_ar":"حُسْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, K, * TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusonaY","text_ar":"حُسْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ham p. 657, and Bd in ii. 77,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, S, Msb),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessed, the quality termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasonN","text_ar":"حَسْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see below; i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(generally the latter,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautiful, comely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHs~n","text_ar":"تحسّن","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"often signifies the same, as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHs~n Einodahu","text_ar":"تحسّن عِنْدَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his estimation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K, TA:) and [in like manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosana","text_ar":"اَحْسَنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd became possessed of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huson","text_ar":"حُسْن"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mughnee in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  One may not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Husona","text_ar":"حُسْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", transferring the dammeh of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":"and making the former letter quiescent, except in one case; because it is [virtually, together with its agent expressed or implied, in this case,] a predicate: [see I'Ak p. 234:] this is allowable only in the case of a verb of praise or dispraise;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Husona","text_ar":"حُسْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in respect of the transference of the medial vowel, being likened to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEoma","text_ar":"نِعْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biy^osa","text_ar":"بِيْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which are originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEima","text_ar":"نَعِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bay^isa","text_ar":"بَيِسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and thus one does in all verbs like these two in meaning: a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lamo yamonaEi Aln~aAsu min~iY maA A^aradotu wa maA\n                      \n                     \n                        A^uEoTiyhimu maA A^araAduwA Husona *aA A^adabaA"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"[Men have not withheld from me what I have desired, nor do I give them what they have desired: good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very good, is this as a mode of conduct!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasuna h`*aA A^adabFA","text_ar":"حَسُنَ هٰذَا اَدَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasuna zayodN","text_ar":"حَسُنَ زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very good"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is Zeyd!"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosino","text_ar":"اَحْسِنْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is Zeyd!"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aHosanahu","text_ar":"مَا اَحْسَنَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (B, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]}}